t. Drawing on a backlist dating to 1893, Voices Revived makes high-quality, peer-reviewed scholarship accessible once again using print-on-demand technology. This title was originally published in 1989.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mrz 2024) 0aLiterature and societyzSpain. 0aRomanticismzSpain. 0aSelf in literature. 0aSpanish literaturexWomen authorsxHistory and criticism. 0aSpanish literaturey19th centuryxHistory and criticism. 0aSubjectivity in literature. 0aWomen and literaturezSpainxHistoryy19th century. 4aRomanticism. 4aSpain. 4aSpanish literature. 4acultural history. 4ahistory of literature. 4ahistory. 4aideology. 4aliterary movements. 4aliterature. 4apresent. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / European / Spanish & Portuguese.2bisacsh40uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052033559240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520335592423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520335592/original  aEBA_EMB  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles